===Noun===
#  A form of visual agnosia characterised by difficulty with face recognition despite intact low-level visual processing.  There are two forms:  acquired prosopagnosia and developmental (also called congenital) prosopagnosia.  Acquired prosopagnosia is usually the result of damage to the occipital and/or temporal cortex, especially to the right hemisphere.  In developmental prosopagnosia, mechanisms carrying out face recognition do not develop normally.  There appear to be a number of developmental difficulties that can produce developmental prosopagnosia including genetic conditions and compromised low-level visual processing early in life.